-add-two-more-football-games-will-play-in/article_884efaa2-5550-11e9-8c8d-a3d24c1b4f74.html|title=Clemson, Georgia add two more football games, will play in 2032, 2033|last=Sapakoff|first=Gene|date=April 2, 2019|website=[[The Post and Courier]]|publisher=[[Evening Post Industries]]|url-status=live|access-date=September 14, 2019}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Records==\n===By team===\n{| class=wikitable style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! Rank !! Team !! Apps !! Record !! Win %\n|-\n ! rowspan=1|1\n | align=left|[[Alabama Crimson Tide football|Alabama]]\n | 6|| 6\u20130 || {{winpct|6|0}}\n|-\n ! rowspan=1|2\n | align=left|[[Tennessee Volunteers football|Tennessee]]\n | 2 || 2\u20130 || {{winpct|1|0}}\n|-\n ! rowspan=2|3\n | align=left|[[LSU Tigers football|LSU]]\n | 1 || 1\u20130 || {{winpct|1|0}}\n|-\n | align=left|[[Ole Miss Rebels football|Ole Miss]]\n | 1 || 1\u20130 || {{winpct|1|0}}\n|-\n ! rowspan=1|5\n | align=left|[[Auburn Tigers football|Auburn]]\n | 3 || 2\u20131 || {{winpct|2|1}}\n|-\n ! rowspan=3|6\n | align=left|[[Boise State Broncos football|Boise State]]\n | 2 || 1\u20131 || {{winpct|1|1}}\n|-\n | align=left|[[Clemson Tigers football team|Clemson]]\n | 2 || 1\u20131 || {{winpct|1|1}}\n|-\n | align=left|[[Georgia Bulldogs football|Georgia]]\n | 2 || 1\u20131 || {{winpct|1|1}}\n|-\n ! rowspan=7|10\n | align=left|[[Duke Blue Devils football|Duke]]\n | 1 || 0\u20131 || {{winpct|0|1}}\n|-\n | align=left|[[Florida State Seminoles football|Florida State]]\n | 1 || 0\u20131 || {{winpct|0|1}}\n|-\n | align=left|[[Georgia Tech Yellow Jackets football|Georgia Tech]]\n | 1 || 0\u20131 || {{winpct|0|1}}\n|-\n | align=left|[[Louisville Cardinals football|Louisville]]\n | 1 || 0\u20131 || {{winpct|0|1}}\n|- \n | align=left|[[North Carolina State Wolfpack football|N.C. State]]\n | 1 || 0\u20131 || {{winpct|0|1}}\n|-\n | align=left|[[Washington Huskies football|Washington]]\n | 1 || 0\u20131 || {{winpct|0|1}}\n|-\n | align=left|[[West Virginia Mountaineers football|West Virginia]]\n | 